<% content_for :title, "Privacy Policy" %>

<article class="prose-legal">
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="doc-meta">Effective date: June 1, 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Veridion Studios Ltd.</p>

  <div class="callout">
    <p>We take your privacy seriously. This policy explains what data we collect, why we collect it, who we share it with, and how you can control it. We will never sell your personal data.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>1. Data we collect</h2>
  <h3>Account data</h3>
  <p>When you register, we collect your email address, name, and any optional profile information you provide (display name, bio, location, website, GitHub username).</p>

  <h3>Identity verification data</h3>
  <p>To comply with financial regulations, we require identity verification for users who transact on the platform. This process is handled by <strong>Stripe Identity</strong>. We receive a verification status and reference ID from Stripe but do not store your government-issued documents.</p>

  <h3>Payment data</h3>
  <p>Payment card details are processed and stored by Stripe. We store only Stripe-issued references (payment intent IDs, transfer IDs, Connect account IDs) — never raw card numbers.</p>

  <h3>Usage data</h3>
  <p>We collect standard server logs including IP addresses, browser type, pages visited, and timestamps. This data helps us diagnose issues and understand platform usage.</p>

  <h3>Communications</h3>
  <p>Messages sent through the platform (quote threads, devlog entries, support conversations) are stored and accessible to the parties involved and to Tessera administrators for moderation purposes.</p>

  <h2>2. How we use your data</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To operate and maintain your account and the services you've requested.</li>
    <li>To process payments and manage escrow on your behalf.</li>
    <li>To verify your identity as required by law and our Terms.</li>
    <li>To send you transactional emails (receipts, milestone notifications, dispute updates).</li>
    <li>To improve and develop the platform using aggregated, anonymised analytics.</li>
    <li>To comply with legal obligations, including anti-money-laundering requirements.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Legal basis for processing (UK/EU)</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Contract:</strong> processing necessary to deliver our services to you.</li>
    <li><strong>Legal obligation:</strong> identity verification and financial record-keeping.</li>
    <li><strong>Legitimate interests:</strong> fraud prevention, platform security, product improvement.</li>
    <li><strong>Consent:</strong> any marketing communications (you can opt out at any time).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Data sharing</h2>
  <p>We share your data only with:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Stripe, Inc.</strong> — for payment processing, identity verification, and Connect payouts. Stripe is a data processor acting on our instructions.</li>
    <li><strong>Sentry</strong> — for error monitoring. Error reports may include anonymised request data.</li>
    <li><strong>Other users on the platform</strong> — your display name, public portfolio, and availability status are visible to other Tessera users as part of normal platform operation.</li>
    <li><strong>Law enforcement</strong> — where required by law or a valid legal order.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We do not sell, rent, or broker your personal data to third parties for marketing purposes.</p>

  <h2>5. Data retention</h2>
  <p>We retain your account data for as long as your account is active, plus 7 years after closure for financial record-keeping purposes. Identity verification records are retained for 5 years as required by applicable AML regulations. You may request deletion of non-financial data at any time.</p>

  <h2>6. Your rights</h2>
  <p>Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Access a copy of the personal data we hold about you.</li>
    <li>Correct inaccurate data.</li>
    <li>Request deletion of your data (subject to legal retention requirements).</li>
    <li>Object to or restrict certain processing.</li>
    <li>Data portability.</li>
    <li>Lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>To exercise any of these rights, contact us at <strong>privacy@veridion.studio</strong>.</p>

  <h2>7. Cookies</h2>
  <p>We use cookies to maintain your session and remember preferences. See our <a href="<%= legal_cookies_path %>">Cookie Policy</a> for full details.</p>

  <h2>8. International transfers</h2>
  <p>Your data may be processed in countries outside the UK/EEA (including the United States, where Stripe is headquartered). We ensure appropriate safeguards are in place, including Standard Contractual Clauses where applicable.</p>

  <h2>9. Security</h2>
  <p>We implement industry-standard security measures including encrypted data in transit (TLS), encrypted passwords (bcrypt), and access controls limiting who within our team can access user data. However, no system is 100% secure and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

  <h2>10. Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>We will notify you of material changes to this Privacy Policy at least 14 days before they take effect. Continued use of the platform constitutes acceptance.</p>

  <h2>11. Contact</h2>
  <p>For privacy enquiries: <strong>privacy@veridion.studio</strong>.</p>
</article>